# Normalise line endings.
#
# core.autocrlf is on for this working tree, so files land as CRLF on Windows. That is fine
# for source Go and JS, but NOT for anything a POSIX shell executes: GitHub Actions runs the
# `run:` blocks in these workflows through bash on Linux runners, where a trailing \r is a
# syntax error ("unexpected token `$'do\r'`"). Pinning them to LF makes the checkout correct
# regardless of who committed from where.
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.yml   text eol=lf
*.yaml  text eol=lf
